Variable: Average Industrial Energy Fuel Efficiency Factor
Information:
| Average efficiency for industrial energy using fuel ``$CAT-FUEL$``. 
 | 
 | **Only Applied to Industrial Energy use**
Loss of electricity in transmission lines. Inflates total demand for electrical energy production.
Fraction of total fuel demand that is imported.
Total exports of a fuel (in units of energy). Used to estimate demand for production in relevant sectors (fugitive emissions and electricity generation).
Specific energy of fuels that are provided in terms of mass.
Notes: See `IEA Bioenergy <https://www.ieabioenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/40_IEAPositionPaperMSW.pdf>` for some estimates for the specific energy of MSW.
